  "prompt": "How one can apply for IIMs after cat results?",
  "response": "To apply for IIMs (Indian Institutes of Management) after CAT results, follow these steps:\n\n1. CAT Preparation and Exam\n- Take the CAT (Common Admission Test)\n- Score well in the exam\n\n2. Check Eligibility Criteria\n- Minimum graduation percentage (usually 50% for general category)\n- Valid CAT score\n- Minimum CAT percentile requirement (typically 80-90 percentile)\n\n3. Online Application Process\n- Visit individual IIM websites\n- Create login credentials\n- Fill out the application form\n- Upload required documents\n- Pay application fee\n\n4. Required Documents\n- CAT score card\n- Academic mark sheets\n- Graduation certificates\n- Work experience certificates (if applicable)\n- Identity proof\n- Passport-sized photographs\n\n5. Selection Process\n- CAT score evaluation\n- Written Ability Test (WAT)\n- Personal Interview (PI)\n- Final merit list preparation\n\n6. Additional Recommendations\n- Research each IIM's specific requirements\n- Prepare for personal interviews\n- Have a strong academic and professional profile\n- Apply to multiple IIMs\n\n7. Important Timeline\n- CAT usually conducted in November\n- Application process starts after CAT results\n- Interviews generally held between January-March\n\nEach IIM has slightly different selection criteria, so carefully check individual institute requirements.",
